  "title": "Fire arrows start fire",
  "description": "A fire arrow can set a block on fire",
  "body": "<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong> <a href=\"https://discord.gg/2CUh6gMuCt\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/discord/1027252425960198165?color=5b6ee1&amp;label=Discord&amp;style=for-the-badge\" alt=\"Discord\" /></a> <a href=\"https://patreon.com/MarsThePlanet\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/endpoint.svg?url=https%3A%2F%2Fshieldsio-patreon.vercel.app%2Fapi%3Fusername%3DMarsThePlanet%26type%3Dpatrons&amp;style=for-the-badge\" alt=\"Support me on Patreon\" /></a> <a href=\"https://www.planetminecraft.com/server/phobos/\"><img title=\"phobos.mcserv.fun\" src=\"https://img.shields.io/endpoint?url=https%3A%2F%2Fminecraft-server-status-badge.vercel.app%2Fapi%2Fserver%2Fphobos.mcserv.fun%3Fport%3D25565&amp;label=anarchy server&amp;style=for-the-badge\" /></a> </strong></h5>\n<div class=\"box p-4 pb-2 project-detail__content\" style=\"text-align: center;\" data-user-content=\"\">\n<p>With this data pack, you can shoot fire arrows that start burning blocks that they hit.</p>\n<p><strong>How does it work?</strong></p>\n<p>When an arrow that is on fire hits any block it will try to set that block on fire and then remove the arrow.</p>\n<p>This makes for more realistic and fun gameplay.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bisecthosting.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/FQLov3P.png\" /></a></p>\n  <img src=\"https://images2.imgbox.com/ad/99/H9AFK6B2_o.png\" alt=\"BLASTING RECIPES\"/>\n  <h1>Blasting Recipes </h1>\n\n<hr>\n<h3><img src=\"https://images2.imgbox.com/07/5b/k4sVmxWC_o.png\" alt=\"BLASTING RECIPES\"/></h3>\n<img src=\"https://images2.imgbox.com/df/8e/GlEVpNFf_o.png\" alt=\"Automatically generates blasting recipes for full blocks of raw metals. (Optionally also smelting recipes)\"/>\n\n<img src=\"https://images2.imgbox.com/df/8e/GlEVpNFf_o.png\" alt=\"Automatically generates blasting recipes for full blocks of raw metals. (Optionally also smelting recipes)\"/>\n<ul>\n<p>